 1→# Pose & Groom example
 2→# pose defines an interface (method signatures).
 3→# groom adds methods to kitty/collar types.
 4→# Types structurally satisfy a pose if they have all required methods.
 5→
 6→# Define an interface
 7→pose Showable {
 8→    meow show() string
 9→}
10→
11→# Kitty definitions
12→kitty Cat {
13→    name: string,
14→    age: int
15→}
16→
17→kitty Dog {
18→    name: string,
19→    good_boy: bool
20→}
21→
22→# Groom: add methods to Cat
23→groom Cat {
24→    meow show() string {
25→        bring self.name + " (age " + to_string(self.age) + ")"
26→    }
27→    meow is_kitten() bool {
28→        bring self.age < 1
29→    }
30→}
31→
32→# Groom: add methods to Dog
33→groom Dog {
34→    meow show() string {
35→        sniff (self.good_boy) {
36→            bring self.name + " (good boy!)"
37→        }
38→        bring self.name
39→    }
40→}
41→
42→# Use methods on kitty instances
43→nyan nyantyu = Cat("Nyantyu", 3)
44→nyan tyako = Cat("Tyako", 0)
45→nyan tyomusuke = Dog("Tyomusuke", yarn)
46→
47→nya(nyantyu.show())
